Files (relative to project root) that implement the /clients routes and their handlers:

- routes/clients.js
- controllers/clients.js

Explanation:
- routes/clients.js defines the /clients endpoints and wires each route to handler functions (router.get('/', getClients), router.post('/', createClient), router.patch('/:id', updateClient), router.delete('/:id', deleteClient), etc.).
- controllers/clients.js contains the actual handler implementations exported and used by the routes: getClient, getClients, createClient, updateClient, deleteClient, and getClientsByUser. These functions perform the database operations (via models/ClientModel.js) and send the HTTP responses.
